</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1871,2004]" lastBlockId="17.[151,1436,151,213]" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="456" pageId="16" pageNumber="455">
Species with a disjunctive range, recorded in 
<collectingCountry box="[717,939,1907,1932]" name="Macedonia" pageId="16" pageNumber="455">FYR of Macedonia</collectingCountry>
, the Greek islands of Chios and Samos, the western (Aegean and Mediterranean regions) and eastern part of 
<collectingCountry box="[874,954,1943,1968]" name="Turkey" pageId="16" pageNumber="455">Turkey</collectingCountry>
(Erzurum) (
<figureCitation box="[1092,1174,1943,1968]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="18.[151,250,956,978]" captionTargetBox="[155,1431,193,934]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[155,1432,193,935]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 17. Distribution of Merodon neonanus sp. n." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/245544/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="455">
Fig. 
<number box="[1143,1174,1944,1968]" pageId="16" pageNumber="455" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
). Elevation range starts from sea level up to 
<quantity box="[398,496,1980,2004]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="16" pageNumber="455" unit="m" value="2400.0">2,400 m</quantity>
. It is primarily found on lower mountains, up to 
<quantity box="[1075,1170,1979,2004]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="16" pageNumber="455" unit="m" value="1500.0">1,500 m</quantity>
(
<figureCitation box="[1189,1276,1979,2004]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="18.[151,250,956,978]" captionTargetBox="[155,1431,193,934]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[155,1432,193,935]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 17. Distribution of Merodon neonanus sp. n." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/245544/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="455">
Fig. 
<number box="[1245,1276,1980,2004]" pageId="16" pageNumber="455" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
). During new investigations in 
<collectingCountry box="[341,422,151,176]" name="Turkey" pageId="17" pageNumber="456">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, adults of 
<taxonomicName box="[536,680,153,176]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="neonanus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[536,680,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="456">M. neonanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[687,750,151,176]" pageId="17" pageNumber="456" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[687,750,151,176]" pageId="17" pageNumber="456">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
and a 
<taxonomicName box="[822,963,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="telmateia">
<emphasis box="[822,963,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="456">M. telmateia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been found on flowers of 
<taxonomicName box="[1316,1436,151,176]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Leontodon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="17" pageNumber="456" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1316,1436,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="456">Leontodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. (Şenol S.G., pers. comm.) (
<figureCitation box="[493,558,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1823,1845]" captionTargetBox="[155,1431,844,1801]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[155,1432,844,1802]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Habitat of Merodon neonanus sp. n. Locality information: Turkey, Muğla, near Çakmak. Male on flower of Leontodon sp. Photo by Ačanski Jelena." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/245528/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="456">
Fig. 
<number box="[545,558,188,212]" pageId="17" pageNumber="456" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
